      <memberdef kind="function" id="struct_a_d_converter_1acbfb668d7b4cfa39aa1a5a5dac3c0e7e" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void task</definition>
        <argsstring>(void)</argsstring>
        <name>task</name>
        <reimplements refid="class_task_1a1951102653a5e603f2131b33d7636232">task</reimplements>
        <param>
          <type>void</type>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para><ref refid="struct_a_d_converter" kindref="compound">ADConverter</ref> task function. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para>Initially the AD converters will be initialized by calling member function initDevice. Then the timers for cyclic automatic sampling are started. Note, that these timer are only created for testing purposes. In productive software the vector of timers is empty. <ref refid="class_i2c_bus" kindref="compound">I2cBus</ref> instance. sensor device will be initialized by call of member function initDevice. For testing purposes a cyclic timer can be activated by commenting in the start method of the timer to initiate a cyclic sampling of the sensor data. <linebreak/>
 Afterwards the function enters the endless loop and wait for messages. Task wakes up when a message is in the mailbox and read the message by calling mailbox read method which returns the pointer pElem to the message. All expected messages will be handled, in case of an unexpected message an error debug message will be triggered. Finally the message will be released by calling class <ref refid="class_pool_elem" kindref="compound">PoolElem</ref> method free, if the pointer pElem is not explicitly set to 0. <linebreak/>
 <linebreak/>
<bold>Message Handling:</bold> <linebreak/>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>eTimerExpired: On sample timer expiry sensor data will be sampled and reported to registered listeners by calling function sample. The pointer pElem will be set to 0, to prevent releasing the message because it is allocated static.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>eAdcReport: On ADC report request sensor data will be sampled and reported to registered listeners by calling function sample. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
