      <memberdef kind="function" id="struct_a_d_converter_1aef4f85575fc282314951dc75e1d4debd" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void autoSample</definition>
        <argsstring>(uint8_t chmask, uint32_t interval, Mbox *listener)</argsstring>
        <name>autoSample</name>
        <param>
          <type>uint8_t</type>
          <declname>chmask</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>uint32_t</type>
          <declname>interval</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="class_mbox" kindref="compound">Mbox</ref> *</type>
          <declname>listener</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Function to start cyclic automatic sampling if specified ADC channels. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>chmask</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Bitmask specifying which channels shall be reported to listener </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>interval</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The sample intervall in millliseconds </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>listener</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>An optional listener, can be NULL if not required</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
The function allocates a structure of type <ref refid="struct_adc_timer_info" kindref="compound">AdcTimerInfo</ref> and assign the this pointer of the class instance and the specified channel bitmask to it. Afterwards it allocates a cyclic timer with duration and period specified by parameter interval and copy the pointer to the timer in vector timers by calling the vector class method push_back. Finally it checks if spezified mailbox pointer listener is not NULL and in this case it registers the listener for the channels specified in channel bitmask chmask by calling member function registerListener. <simplesect kind="note"><para>This function is only implemented for testing purposes, in productive software this function is not called. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
