        <briefdescription>
<para>Send ADC data to optional registered listener for specified channel. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>channel</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The specified ADC channel </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>raw</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The measured ADC raw data </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>mv</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The measured ADC data converted to millivolt</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
The function checks if there is a listener registered for the specified channel and if the pointer to listener mailbox in array adc_listeners is not NULL, it requests a message from message pool, set message type to eAdcData, set eADConverter as sender and send message to the listener&apos;s mailbox. </para>
