        <briefdescription>
<para>Function to sample ADC data for specified channels. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>chmask</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The channel bitmask, specifying the channels which shall be sampled</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
The function allocates a structure of type struct adc_sequence which defines an ADC sampling sequence with an 16 bit unsigned integer type. Than it enters a loop over the ADC channels and check if bit at position i is set in channel bitmask chmask. If bit is set, it initialize the struct sequence of type adc_sequence with the information provided array <ref refid="classadc__channels" kindref="compound">adc_channels</ref> of type struct adc_dt_spec at index i by calling function adc_sequence_init_dt provided by Zephyr ADC API. With call of function adc_read also provided by Zephyr ADC API it reads the raw value into structure sequence. Afterwards the raw value will be assigned to to local varible val_mv and converted to millivolt by call of function adc_raw_to_millivolts_dt also provided by Zephyr ADC API, which uses the ADC specification from device tree from structure struct adc_dt_spec provided by array <ref refid="classadc__channels" kindref="compound">adc_channels</ref> at position i. Finally the listeners will be informed by calling member function notifyListener. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
