    <briefdescription>
<para>AD converter driver class derived from task base class. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Detailed Description </title><para>The AD converter driver class handle the reception of the analog values, convert them into digital values and report them to the registered listener task on request. For testing purposes cyclic timer handling is implemented and can be used for automatic cyclic sampling. The timers are organized in a vector and will be allocated in the autoSample method, which is only called by inactive testing scenarios. <linebreak/>
The AD converter class provides methods to sample the data of the provided AD channels, to initialize the AD devices and to report the data to the registered listener tasks. It uses the public zephyr API for the sensor driver. See details in <ulink url="https://docs.zephyrproject.org/apidoc/latest/group__adc__interface.html">Zephyr ADC API documentation</ulink> and for details of the <ulink url="https://docs.zephyrproject.org/latest/hardware/peripherals/adc.html">ADC channel configuration in the devicetree</ulink> <bold>Message Interaction:</bold><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Receive<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Timer interrupt callback (only for testing purposes)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>AD converter task (self, only for testing purposes)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Battery manager task</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Transmit<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Battery manager task</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>AD converter task (self, transmission in timer callback, only for testing purposes) </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
